				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">and NO Fal this is not an attack on him! <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />
Just he had a good point which I wish to rebutt. I'ts an interesting and important subject for debate.
<br />

<br />
Ok, you point out smoking shouldnt be much of a danger unless exposed on frequent basis. I'd like to point out:
<br />

<br />
1) Well peopel are exposed to cig smoke a lot, which is why smoking is being banned in public places and the like. One reason I hate pubs, except in the quiet hours, is because they are choked with fag smoke <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="Sad" border="0" /> (Note UK defination of "fag"). People have been subjected to that crap for hours on end in pubs, cubs, workplace, cinema you name it. Most workplaces have limits for exposure to hazardous materials..cigarette smoke IS hazardous..so it's mostly banned, and for safety reasons in engineering and the like.
<br />
My best mate's girlfriend smokes and they have two babies, that's damn stupid for the kids' health, but she can't help it because, tada, fags are so damned addictive.
<br />

<br />
2) Cigarettes are a general hazard due to fire. Despite the really great and stringent fire codes and safer materials, fire is a deadly hazard. Note tragedies in several US night spots within the last year. Going around with a BURNING item is *stupid*, any where else you'd say a person going aroudn with a burning item for hours at a time not in a safety holder is STUPID, and with good reason. But because of the "social" aspect of smoking, this isn't challenged. Chewing tobacco maybe gross and messy but it's miles safer than going aorudn with a naked flame, isn't it? <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" />
<br />
Smoking is one of the major causes of accidental fires, which cost many lives, homes, buisnesses each year. Accidents happen but those are....
<br />

<br />
3) Crime. The new drug of choice to sell is, very seriously, cigarettes. It's become a big issue here. Since cigarettes are now so expensive, drug "barons" are switching to cigaerettes and making more money than they do from heroin etc! Remmeber, cigarettes *ARE* more addictive than heroin, this has been proven conclusvely by numerous studies. You get hooked incredibly fast and have a far higher chance of smoking again than going back to heroin after quitting. Since society doesn't view selling cigarettes as scummy as heroin, there is less risk for the drug barons.
<br />
Therefore, illegal cigarette trading is a HUGE profit industry.
<br />
But..these folk who are behind it are scum. I know a few, "gangsters" are NOT charismatic fun nice interesting people..they are sick, brutal murdering vermin. They maim and kill folk, and don't give a damn if you are hooked on heroin or nicotine, they don't care for you or any one else AT ALL.
<br />
--Ideally those hooked on drugs, including cigarettes should get cheap, basic but as safe-as-possible goods provided on prescription, thus ruining the market for the gangsters, cutting down on the spread of the crap. Think that's silly? Hm IIRC a pack of 20 fags costs £3:20 or so legit here, thats money folk could spend on far better things, especially if poor, Criminal gangs sell them for I think about £2 per pack, so if oyu are on a low income...
<br />

<br />
Folk should have the right to smoke if they chose, but, as always with anything, a drug, a tool, a device, it's down to personal responsibility and *society behaving  with compassion, thought and safety*.
<br />
When society is stupid, there's problem. Cars, drugs, firearms, alcohol, cigarettes all cause real trouble because of the attitude towards them and thus how they are dealt with. Tobacco is about the most WORTHLESS of all the things we abuse.
